{
  "texts": [
    "In our work, transformer layers contain 12 attention heads, with dimension 768, leading to d k = 64.",
    "Since the multi-head attention layer is equivariant to permutations of the input tokens, we use rotary positional embeddings 58 to enable learning of sequential features.",
    "The self-attention block is complemented by residual blocks, a feed-forward neural network and layer normalization steps, resulting in a final output with the dimension [T, 768] (see Supplementary Fig. 1 for more details).",
    "Following ref.",
    "24, we use prenormalization to increase stability and no dropout 24."
  ]
}